{"timestamp":1774434250791,"source_app":"agentic-harness","session_id":"fa565409-7377-413e-9363-9fde373e86ce","hook_event_type":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_0131ucAipBeRg2LZnCZJ5fLY","payload":{"session_id":"fa565409-7377-413e-9363-9fde373e86ce","transcript_path":"/Users/auto/.claude/projects/-Users-auto-agentic-harness-apps-mas-trees-7a36499d/fa565409-7377-413e-9363-9fde373e86ce.jsonl","cwd":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/7a36499d","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PreToolUse","tool_name":"Write","tool_input":{"file_path":"/Users/auto/agentic-harness/apps/mas/trees/7a36499d/specs/issue-7a36499d-adw-5d0e6cf3-sdlc_planner-remove-footer-from-plans-page.md","content":"# Plan: Remove footer from plans page\n\n## Task Description\nRemove the `<footer>` element from the `plans` variant merch card render layout. The footer currently contains the secure transaction label and the CTA slot (`slot name=\"footer\"`). The goal is to fully delete the footer markup from the rendered output \u2014 not hide it with CSS. Dead CSS targeting the footer should also be removed. The scope is limited to the `plans` variant (including `plans-education`, `plans-students`); the `plans-v2` variant is a separate class and must not be touched unless explicitly scoped.\n\n## Relevant Files\n\n- `web-components/src/variants/plans.js` \u2014 **edit**: remove `${this.secureLabelFooter}` from `renderLayout()`; remove footer-specific CSS from `variantStyle`; audit `adjustSlotPlacement` for null-safety now that `footer` will be absent from the shadow DOM\n- `web-components/src/variants/plans.css.js` \u2014 **edit**: remove any global CSS rules that target `merch-card[variant^=\"plans\"] footer` (if any exist)\n- `web-components/src/variants/variant-layout.js` \u2014 **read-only**: understand `secureLabelFooter` and `secureLabel` base implementations (no changes needed here)\n\n## Step by Step Tasks\n\n### 1. Remove `secureLabelFooter` from `Plans.renderLayout()`\n- In `web-components/src/variants/plans.js`, locate `renderLayout()` (line ~329)\n- Delete the `${this.secureLabelFooter}` template expression from the returned html template literal\n- The `<slot></slot>` default slot after it must remain in place\n\n### 2. Remove footer-specific CSS from `Plans.variantStyle`\n- In the same file, locate `static variantStyle = css\\`...\\``\n- Remove the rule block `:host([variant^='plans']) footer { ... }` (lines ~441\u2013444)\n- Remove the rule block `:host([variant^='plans']) footer ::slotted([slot='addon']) { ... }` (lines ~417\u2013420)\n- Remove the rule block `:host([variant='plans']) .wide-footer #stock-checkbox { ... }` (lines ~422\u2013424) \u2014 only needed when footer is present\n- Keep all other CSS rules untouched\n\n### 3. Audit `adjustSlotPlacement` for footer-null safety\n- In `adjustSlotPlacement()` (line ~87), `shadowRoot.querySelector('footer')` will now return `null`\n- All existing accesses already use optional chaining (`footer?.classList`), so no runtime error will occur\n- Verify no path performs a non-optional access on `footer` \u2014 if found, add `?.` guard\n\n### 4. Check `plans.css.js` for global footer rules\n- Scan `web-components/src/variants/plans.css.js` for any rules targeting `footer` within plans variants\n- If found, remove those rules\n\n### 5. Validate syntax\n- Run `node --check web-components/src/variants/plans.js`\n- Run `node --check web-components/src/variants/plans.css.js`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- The `Plans.renderLayout()` no longer emits a `<footer>` element\n- No `display:none` or visibility tricks are used \u2014 the footer markup is absent from the DOM\n- CSS rules that exclusively targeted the now-removed footer are deleted\n- `plans-v2.js` is unchanged\n- `variant-layout.js` is unchanged\n- `node --check` passes on all modified files\n- Other variant pages (segment, product, catalog, etc.) are unaffected\n\n## Validation Commands\n- `node --check web-components/src/variants/plans.js`\n- `node --check web-components/src/variants/plans.css.js`\n"},"tool_use_id":"toolu_0131ucAipBeRg2LZnCZJ5fLY"}}
